HEADWORD: Snacot
<hw>Snac"ot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Said to be corrupted
fr. NL. <ets>syngnathus</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>sy`n</grk> together +
<grk>gna`qos</grk> jaw, because the jaws can be only slightly
separated.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A pipefish of the genus
<gen>Syngnathus</gen>. See <er>Pipefish</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

